article.headline: Grambling 88, Texas College 70
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Grambling State shot 61.4 percent from the floor, led by guard Brion Rush who scored 22 points in the Tigers' 88-70 season-opening win against Texas College at Memorial Gym on Tuesday night. In addition to the double-figure scoring, Rush, a senior, posted his first career triple-double, grabbing 10 rebounds and recording 10 assists. Sophomore guard Andre' Ratliff added 18 points, connecting on six-of-10 3-pointers along with seven rebounds, four assists and two steals. Senior guard Donte' Gordon had 17 points and junior forward Anthony Williams added 15. Texas College was led by sophomore guard Mario Kersey who had 20 points on nine of 18 shooting along with five assists and one rebound. Senior forward Jamar Adams added 17 points. Grambling state led by just one point at the half, 40-39.
